</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/6/03 12:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2026.topic&index=81>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Final Fantasy XI</span><hr size=1> Here is a tidbit I found interesting...<br>
<br>
To new players: You might be puzzling a bit as to how this conquest system works. To explain it simply, when your country is dominant in the region you are in, you can get crystals (lots of loot, easier starting cash), and things are a little easier. Less scary mobs spawning right outside the gates <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Also, if it is the region surrounding your city, if you are dominant, the merchants sell better stuff, possibly for lower prices (ex: last sat on Midgard, Windurst owned Sarutabaruta, and a black mage could buy poison, and blind, and bind in town. Now that we no longer have control, these spells are not available from merchants). <br>
<br>
I am sure there is more that is affected but I am pretty new also. NOW! To the important information... <br>
<br>
How do the beastmen, or the players gain control of a region? Everytime you the player kills a critter, or a Yagudo, or anything that we all know really had it coming anyway (damn crawlers) Your country gains points for that region. Everytime a PLAYER dies... the beastmen gain points from that region. I am not clear on how the numbers work, but to put it simply, at least around Windurst on Midgard, people are dying too much :-D <br>
<br>
So we have established that when you die, not only does it affect you, but indirectly affects every other player from your country, in that region. <br>
<br>
Having established this, the lessons that are to be taken here   <br>
<br>
1) It DOES benefit you to help others, no matter what. If they dont die, your better off. <br>
<br>
2) It hurts everyone when YOU die. So dont wait until you know its just gonna take 2 or 3 more blows and your dead... if it looks like you are in trouble, call for help immiediately! The game has a great system for allowing people to come help you, but they might need to get there first. <br>
<br>
3) At any moment during a fight, calling for help shouldnt be more then a few keystrokes away. You can either use control+G, or using the combat menu, hit the right arrow, with disengage highlighted, and hit enter. <br>
<br>
4) This one should be familiar to EQ people: If you need help, and people are around to help you, DO NOT RUN. 9 times outta 10 the mob is still beating the life out of you, and all that is happening is everyone that wants to help you, has to try and chase down the mob. The only time this doesnt apply is if you are in the middle of nowhere, and there is nobody around. Just remember to call for help so people see your Mob on their radar/compass thingy. <br>
<br>
5) Quick explanation of calling for help: when you call for help, it allows anyone to start beating on your mob, as well as making its name appear next to the compass of nearby players, and a little red arrow appear on their compass, pointing to your mob. <br>
<br>
<br>
Nice to know!! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=cyradus>Cyradus</A> at: 11/6/03 12:45 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=2026.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=2026.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=2026.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showMessageRange?topicID=2026.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a> <b>5</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=2026.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=2026.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2026.topic&index=81><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.threadControl?topicID=2026.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2026.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2026.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif w